
## 📌 Project Overview

Today's lab focused on one of Git's most powerful features: **Cherry-Pick**.

Unlike merging an entire branch, Git Cherry-Pick allows developers to copy a **single commit** from one branch into another. This is especially useful when only one specific change is ready for production while the remaining work is still under development.

In this lab, the development team had two branches:

- master
- feature

A developer working on the **feature** branch needed only one commit (`Update info.txt`) merged into **master**, without merging the unfinished feature branch.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Navigate Git branches
- Identify a specific commit by commit message
- Cherry-pick a commit into another branch
- Push the updated master branch to the remote repository

